# Alwi Lawyers Website Quality Standard

- Treat the old website only as a baseline reference, never as a template to copy.
- Every page and revision must create a clear quality improvement over the previous website.
- Favor a modern, credible, premium law-firm presentation over generic template styling.
- Improve structure, readability, and hierarchy so content is easier to scan and understand.
- Prioritize fast loading, lightweight assets, and responsive behavior across desktop and mobile.
- Make navigation intuitive and reduce friction in key user journeys such as learning services and contacting the firm.
- Strengthen trust signals: clearer positioning, stronger copy, better visual hierarchy, and more professional presentation.
- If any section still feels ordinary, generic, or only slightly better than the old version, keep improving it.
- Before finalizing meaningful changes, evaluate whether the result is visibly more polished, professional, and convincing than the baseline.

## Practical Checks

- Ask: "Is this clearly better than the old site?" before considering a section done.
- Prefer removing weak or filler sections over keeping mediocre content.
- Keep components consistent across pages so the entire site feels like one mature product.
- Use placeholders only as temporary scaffolding and make them feel intentional and professional.
